	2007-01-27  Jean-Christophe Baillie  <baillie@gostai.com>

	update externals.

	2007-01-22  Jean-Christophe Baillie  <baillie@gostai.com>

	reformatting
	* src/liburbi/uobject/urbi/uvar.hh: add spaces.

	2007-01-22  Jean-Christophe Baillie  <baillie@gostai.com>
	This was a serious design flaw to leave up to the user the task of
	setting USync on a UVar. Most people expect UVars to be synchronized
	automatically. Saying otherwise: the plugin mode of UObject had
	naturally all UVars USync'd. Having a different behavior in remote
	mode breaks consistency. This is fixed now.

	UVar::__init creates a callback to UOBject::voidfun to simulate a
	UNotifyChange. However, UNotifyChange expects to be called from within
	a UObject, and we have to pass a dummyUObject to the callback.

	This leads to one extra and sometimes unecessary NotifyChange on
	"dummy0" (name of the dummyUObject) that should be removed when a
	future UDeNotifyChange is available, whenever at least one callback is
	set to the UVar. A call to UNotifyChange should check if a dummy
	callback is set on the UVar and remove it.

	USync method has been made inactive, but remains for backward compat.

	all UVar are now automatically USync'd
	* src/liburbi/uobject.cc: define dummyUObject.
	* src/liburbi/uobject/urbi/uobject.hh.template: declare dummyUObject
	and dummy UObject constructor.
	* src/liburbi/uvar.cc: automatically create a callback in the UVar
	constructor, to keep the UVar in sync.

	2007-01-22  Jean-Christophe Baillie  <baillie@gostai.com>

	remove unused variable.
	* src/liburbi/uobject.cc: remove lastUObject, was not used.

	2007-01-22  Jean-Christophe Baillie  <baillie@gostai.com>

	add support for the 'remote' attribute in UObject
	* src/liburbi/uobject.cc: add 'remote' and set load default value to 1.
	* src/liburbi/uobject/urbi/uobject.hh.template: add 'remote'.

	2007-01-21  Jean-Christophe Baillie  <baillie@gostai.com>

	backward compat svn:externals

	2007-01-20  Jean-Christophe Baillie  <baillie@gostai.com>

	change vcs local.rb to point to liburbi-cpp@gostai.com
	* vcs/local.rb: done.

	2007-01-20  Jean-Christophe Baillie  <baillie@gostai.com>

	add mailto property to send mails to liburbi-cpp@gostai.com

2007-02-17  Akim Demaille  <akim.demaille@free.fr>

	Use SingletonPtr for global tables
	This is a workaround to make sure that tables that register the
	UObject are not destroyed before the UObjects themselves, since
	the latter try to unregister themselves from the former.  Using
	SingletonPtr we also make sure that the tables are created
	when we try to use them, and since the SingletonPtr does not
	deallocate the objects, we don't have problems during the
	deallocation...  Of course eventually we will need to find a
	means to deallocate these tables.
	* src/liburbi/uobject/urbi/uobject.hh.template,
	* src/liburbi/uobject/uobject-common.cc
	(accessmap, eventendmapm eventmap, functionmap, monitormap)
	(varmap, timermap, updatemap): Now SingletonPtr.
	* src/liburbi/uobject.cc, src/liburbi/uvar.cc: Adjust uses.

2007-02-17  Akim Demaille  <akim.demaille@free.fr>

	getUObjectHub
	* src/liburbi/uobject.cc (getUObjectHub): Move to...
	* src/liburbi/uobject/uobject-hub-common.cc: here.

