2007-01-25  Akim Demaille  <demaille@gostai.com>

	2007-01-22  Jean-Christophe Baillie  <baillie@gostai.com>

	reformatting
	* src/liburbi/uobject/urbi/uvar.hh: add spaces.

	2007-01-22  Jean-Christophe Baillie  <baillie@gostai.com>
	This was a serious design flaw to leave up to the user the task of
	setting USync on a UVar. Most people expect UVars to be synchronized
	automatically. Saying otherwise: the plugin mode of UObject had
	naturally all UVars USync'd. Having a different behavior in remote
	mode breaks consistency. This is fixed now.

	UVar::__init creates a callback to UOBject::voidfun to simulate a
	UNotifyChange. However, UNotifyChange expects to be called from within
	a UObject, and we have to pass a dummyUObject to the callback.

	This leads to one extra and sometimes unecessary NotifyChange on
	"dummy0" (name of the dummyUObject) that should be removed when a
	future UDeNotifyChange is available, whenever at least one callback is
	set to the UVar. A call to UNotifyChange should check if a dummy
	callback is set on the UVar and remove it.

	USync method has been made inactive, but remains for backward compat.

	all UVar are now automatically USync'd
	* src/liburbi/uobject.cc: define dummyUObject.
	* src/liburbi/uobject/urbi/uobject.hh.template: declare dummyUObject
	and dummy UObject constructor.
	* src/liburbi/uvar.cc: automatically create a callback in the UVar
	constructor, to keep the UVar in sync.

	2007-01-22  Jean-Christophe Baillie  <baillie@gostai.com>

