2007-01-14  Jean-Christophe Baillie  <baillie@gostai.com>

	The UObject API, however bad looking or problematic it looks should
	not be modified in the short term to avoid backward incompatibilities
	that we cannot handle right now. Future rewritting with a fresh and
	new (non conflicting) API will come in the future, until then we fix
	what is existing or provide backward compatible alternatives.

	JCB: As a rule also, remember that any change impacting the API or GUI
	of our products should get my approval first, and, more generally, be
	necessarily a collegial decision/agreement between the members of the
	kernel team.

	revert API change
	* examples/urbibandwidth.cc: done.
	* examples/urbisendsound.cc: done.
	* examples/urbisound.cc: done.
	* examples/urbitalkie.cc: done.
	* liburbi/uabstractclient.cc: done.
	* liburbi/uconversion.cc: done.
	* liburbi/uobject/urbi/ubinary.hh: done.
	* liburbi/uobject/uvalue-common.cc: done.
	* liburbi/usyncclient.cc: done.
	* liburbi/uvar.cc: done.

2007-01-12  Matthieu Nottale  <nottale@gostai.com>

	Fix binary parser bug.
